article.headline: VIRGINIA TECH 71, (12) TEXAS TECH 70 (OT)
article.story:
LAS VEGAS (Ticker) -- Carrie Mason scored 12 points and Erin 
Gibson and Nare Diawara added 11 apiece as Virginia Tech upset
No. 12 Texas Tech, 71-70, in overtime in the championship game
of the Duel in the Desert.

Mason hit two free throws to make it 71-68 with 29 seconds
remaining. After Cisti Greenwalt's basket pulled Texas Tech
within a point, Mason missed a pair from the line with eight
seconds to go.

But Virginia Tech (7-2), which trailed by as many as 13 in the
second half, escaped with the victory when Texas Tech's Chelsey
Dobbs missed a jumper from the top of the key at the buzzer.

After Mason made a pair of 3-pointers to give the Hokies a 54-51
lead with 4:03 left in the second half, Texas Tech's Kirby
Copeland converted 1-of-2 from the line with 28 seconds left in
regulation to force overtime at 60-60.

LaToya scored 23 points on 9-of-13 shooting for the Red Raiders
(6-2). Greenwalt contributed 14 points and 12 rebounds.

Dobbs also scored 14 points but made just 6-of-20 shots. Alesha
Robertson chipped in with 11 points for the Red Raiders, who
shot only 37.5 percent (24-of-64) from the field.

Virginia Tech shot just 25 percent (9-of-36) in the first half
and trailed, 27-19, at the break. But the Hokies improved to 45
percent (14-of-31) in the second half and finished at 36 percent
(26-of-72).
